<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="SB0227" sponsor="Ronald M. Winterton" designation="SB" otherSponsor="" otherHouse="House" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL1201" date="1/30/2026 09:01:743" printDate="01-30 09:52" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>6</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="E" src="code" buid="1" uid="C78B-8-S204_2026050620260506" sort="78B08 02040020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">78B-8-204</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="5" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Punitive Damages Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Ronald M. Winterton</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>House Sponsor: </otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill enacts provisions relating to limitations on liability for punitive damages.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">defines "motor vehicle";</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">provides a limit on an award of punitive damages resulting from a personal injury claim <ln numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10"/>that involves a motor vehicle; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">provides a limit on the attorney fees related to an award of punitive damages.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="13">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="15">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saent numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="78B-8-204" src="code" uid="C78B-8-S204_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="78B08 02040020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18"><bold>78B-8-204</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="19"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="78B-8-204" type="enact" src="code" uid="C78B-8-S204_2026050620260506" sort="78B08 02040020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="1-2" number="78B-8-204" type="enact"><secline lineno="21">Section 1. Section <bold>78B-8-204</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="22"><bold>78B-8-204<parens/>. Limitations on award of punitive damages for a personal injury <ln numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-3"/>claim involving a motor vehicle.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="11" groupid="8" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this section, "motor vehicle" means the same as that term is defined in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-5"/>Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="41-1a-102">41-1a-102</xref>.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-2" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="32" groupid="25" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">If the basis for punitive damages under Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="78B-8-201">78B-8-201</xref> is based on the tortfeasor's <ln numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-7"/>operation of a motor vehicle and the cause of action arises out of a personal injury claim, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-8"/>an award of punitive damages may not exceed an amount equal to the greater of:</amend><subsection ssid="1-7" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-9" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="38" groupid="30" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">the sum of:</amend><subsection ssid="1-10" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-10" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="53" groupid="42" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">two times the amount of economic damages; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-8" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-11" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="43" groupid="34" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">an amount equal to any noneconomic damages not exceeding $750,000; or</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-9" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-12" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="48" groupid="38" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">$200,000.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-11" dnum="_-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-13" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="54" groupid="43" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">If a court awards a person punitive damages in accordance with this section, attorney <ln numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-14"/>fees for the person may not exceed 25% of the amount of the total award of punitive <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-15"/>damages.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="5" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="36">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="37"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>1-30-26 9:52 AM</tm></rev></foot></leg>